%N A336348 Square spiral of positive integers constructed by greedy algorithm, such that for any k > 0, k appears exactly k times, and all occurrences of k lie on the same row or on the same column.
%C A336348 This sequence can be seen as a two-dimensional variant of A002024.
%C A336348 For symmetry reasons, we obtain the same sequence when considering a clockwise or a counterclockwise square spiral, or when initially moving towards any unit direction.
